The paper deals with the problem of characterizing testable graph properties, which is a fundamental problem in the area of property testing. This falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The focus of the paper is on planar graphs, which suggests that it could also belong to Computational Geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves analyzing the random neighbor oracle model, which is a common tool in the study of property testing and falls under the category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves analyzing the structure of graphs, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the properties of graphs, which falls under the category of Graph Theory (cs.GT).
